A minSP is a 1 √Ä 2 isolated minSP if the cycles contained in the minSP are either isolated 2-cycles or 1-cycles. Let sm be the number of 1 √Ä 2 isolated minSP s with at least two isolated 2-cycles and ss be the number of 1 √Ä 2 isolated minSP s with exactly one isolated 2-cycle in G5s√∞A; B√û. By the definitions, all S-MSPs in G5s√∞A; B√û are 1 √Ä 2 isolated minSP s with exactly one isolated 2-cycle, and the number of S-MSPs in G5s√∞A; B√û is also ss. The total number of 1 √Ä 2 isolated minSP s in G5s√∞A; B√û is sm √æ ss. Let sa denote the number of 1 √Ä 2minSP s in G5s√∞A; B√û, each of them contains at least one arbitrary 2-cycle.
Proposition 1. If a minSP of G5s√∞A; B√û contains a related 2-cycle, then the minSP contains at least one arbitrary cycle.

The proof of the proposition is exactly the same as that of Lemma 3 in the full version of [4]. By Proposition 1, we immediately have the following lemma:
Lemma 10. The total number of 1 √Ä 2minSP s in G5s√∞A; B√û is sm √æ ss √æ sa.

