Proof. By definition, G5s√∞A; B√û contains sir isolated 2-cycles as removable 2-cycles of some RS-MSPs. Thus, zout ! sir. Consider the st S-MSPs in G5s√∞A; B√û that correspond to CRS-MSPs in the unsigned breakpoint graph and are
not transformed into RS-MSPs in Procedure Creating
Remove (Fig. 6). We want to show that such st S-MSPs correspond to st isolated 2-cycles outside minSP s that cannot be removable 2-cycles. Therefore, we can conclude that zout ! st √æ sir.
First, consider the case that st ¬º 1. Let I ¬º xi; xi√æ1; . . . ; xj√Ä1; xj denote such an S-MSP. The unique 2-cycle in I is C ¬º r√∞xi√û; l√∞xi√æ1√û; l√∞xj√û; r√∞xj√Ä1√û; r√∞xi√û. Without loss of generality, we assume that G√∞A; B√û contains gray edge √∞xi; xj√æ1√û. (See Fig. 5a.) The reason that I is not transformed into RS-MSP in Procedure CreatingRemove (Fig. 6) is that the key gray edge √∞l√∞xi√û; l√∞xj√æ1√û√û has two conflicting 2-cycles in M. Let C1 and C2 be the two conflicting 2-cycles, where C1 ¬º r√∞xi√Ä1√û; l√∞xi√û; r√∞xj√æ1√û; l√∞xj√æ2√û; r√∞xi√Ä1√û, and C2 contains black edge √∞r√∞xj√û; l√∞xj√æ1√û√û. (See Fig. 5a.) A conflicting 2-cycle can be a related 2-cycle or an isolated 2-cycle. Now, we prove that C2 is an isolated 2-cycle. First, the cycle C2 cannot be related to C since C is an isolated 2-cycle. Suppose C2 is related to C1. The two gray edges √∞l√∞xi√û; r√∞xj√æ1√û√û and √∞r√∞xi√Ä1√û; l√∞xj√æ2√û√û in C1 are parallel. If C1 and C2 are in a related

CUI ET AL.: A √∞1:5 √æ √û-Approximation ALGORITHM FOR UNSIGNED TRANSLOCATION DISTANCE

